Bring a large pot of water to a boil; season with salt. Saute garlic with olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat until slightly yellow in color, about 1 minute. Add peppers and oregano; saute for 4-5 minutes. Add chickpeas; saute for an additional minute. Cook pasta 2 minutes less than package directions. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup (125ml) of pasta cooking liquid. Add pasta and reserved pasta cooking liquid to skillet with the peppers and chickpeas mixture; cook over high heat until thickened. Season with salt and pepper. Top with Romano cheese before serving.